abstract_ssm: Majority Report (1971-1979) was a New York based feminist newspaper published by an editorial collective and dedicated to the women's liberation movement. Majority Report's research files dated 1969-1979 are on feminists, popular, political and literary figures, movement activism and events related to women's rights issues.  The files contain clippings from various feminist and mainstream publications, select issues of publications including the Majority Report, correspondence, press releases, writings, notes, printed ephemera and photographs.
